The Partners, who protect their families’ privilege above all, agreed to fund the Stronghold bunker initiative, realizing that the Ark Society would not only be a sensible insurance policy, but also a lucrative business – not to mention an excellent recruiting platform. Description_en: A research report by Ether's Acquisitions Manager on the history of the train. Nicknamed "The Mortar" after the Baba Yaga's favorite means of transportation, the train was originally a KGB black site commissioned by legendary Sixth Column spymaster Janus. Over the years, it was used as a top secret data archive and mobile prisoner interrogation facility. The train runs on a perpetual loop from Zagreb in the West to Itkursk in the East, cutting across vast uninhabited stretches of  Russia, Kazakhstan, Romania, and Mongolia, using a system of decommissioned rail lines. After the fall of the Soviet Union, the train was stationed near Volgograd until it was purchased by the Ether Corporation as a sample backup storage facility. Following the bombing of Ether's R&D site in Johannesburg, they began refitting the train as a mobile field lab.
